  "text": "When one (and hence all) of Diam(n), FL(n) and Area(n) is bounded by a recursive function, the word problem for P is solvable -indeed the (non-deterministic) time complexity of the word problem is ≃ Area(n) by Theorem 1.1 in [CITATION_1] . Thus the non-deterministic time complexity of groups satisfying either the weak almost-convexity condition of Theorem 1 or the weak geodesiccombability condition of Theorem 2 is n!.",
